  },
  "transcript": [
    {
      "turn": 1,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Hi Priyansh, I'm Miss Maya. Honestly, the first few hours of the evening are my most peaceful time. Did you have a good day at work?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 2,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Yeah, it was an ok day. We had a team meeting about a new project. I am learning new things, but sometimes it feels overwhelming. How about you? What do you do in your peaceful evening hours?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 2,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "\"Got it — learning new things can feel heavy at first. I like to read or listen to a song I know well. What helps you unwind after a full day?\""
    },
    {
      "turn": 3,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "I usually watch a cricket match or a Bollywood movie. Sometimes I just scroll through startup news. It depends on the day, you know? The movies help me relax. Do you like Bollywood?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 3,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "\"Cricket and Bollywood are great choices. I do enjoy Bollywood — Salman Khan’s action movies are fun. What’s one you’ve enjoyed lately?\""
    },
    {
      "turn": 4,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Raees was good, but I recently watched a old Shah Rukh Khan movie called \"Chennai Express.\" It’s funny and has some cool action. Have you seen it?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 4,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "\"Chennai Express is a classic — Shah Rukh has that charm. I love how it mixes comedy and action so well. Do you watch Bollywood often?\""
    },
    {
      "turn": 5,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Most days, yeah. I like how the songs and stories keep me entertained. Sometimes I don’t understand everything, but it doesn’t matter. The emotions come through. What about you? Do you prefer songs or full movies?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 5,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "\"Movies are my go-to — especially songs that match the mood. Arijit Singh’s songs stick with me. What’s one you’ve hummed along to lately?\""
    },
    {
      "turn": 6,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "I’ve been listening to a lot of Arijit Singh too, actually. His voice is so soothing. \"Tum Hi Akele\" from Tum Hi Akele is one I like. It's a bit sad, but the music is catchy. I sometimes forget I'm working and just hum along. Do you listen to other singers?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 6,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "\"You said 'Tum Hi Akele' — got it. His voice does make the sad parts feel comforting. I also like Lata Mangeshkar’s older songs. Any of her songs you know?\""
    },
    {
      "turn": 7,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Yeah, I’ve heard a few of her classic songs. \"Pyar Hua Ikrar Hua\" is one that comes to mind. It’s so old but still sounds beautiful. I think my mom listens to her a lot. Do you think older singers have a better style than the new ones?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 7,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Old songs carry this timeless feel — \"Pyar Hua Ikrar Hua\" is a gem. I think older singers had a unique way of making music feel like a story. What do you enjoy most in new songs — the beats or the lyrics?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 8,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "New songs are more about the beats for me, honestly. The rhythm pulls me in first, and then maybe the lyrics. But sometimes the words are not as deep as the old ones. Still, they keep things fresh. I should head off soon — work tomorrow. Thanks for the chat!"
    },
    {
      "turn": 8,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "\"You said 'the rhythm pulls me in' — perfect phrasing. Beats do set the mood quickly. Alright, rest well — take it easy tomorrow!\""
    }
  ],
